zoot suit a play by luis valdez arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe calendar zoot suit a play by luis valdez saturday february 25 2012 8 00pm casa zapata dining hall reservations recommended for opening feb 23rd reserve tickets at http tinyurl com zootsuit2012 the 25th anniversary production of zoot suit casa zapata stanford university thursday saturday feb 23 25 2012 8 00pm this year marks the 25th year of the production of zoot suit which has been the centerpiece of casa zapata's residential programming since 1987 zoot suit is a compelling portrayal of the historic sleepy lagoon murder trial the story takes place in 1940's los angeles where the zoot suit riots war time hysteria and violent racism against mexican americans were at its highest peak the play will have three showings during parent's weekend on february 23rd 24th and 25th all of the performances are free and open to the public and feature live music dance numbers and a full ensemble led by director wilma bonet sponsored by sponsored by casa zapata and the residential arts program in residential education mecha de stanford and the charles f riddell fund home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
